{
  "title": "Wurl",
  "children": [
    {
      "title": "About",
      "lines": [
        "Physically-modeled",
        "Wurlitzer 200A electric",
        "piano. Port of",
        "OpenWurli (hal0zer0,",
        "GPL-3.0).",
        "",
        "Modal reed oscillator",
        "(7 modes, Euler-",
        "Bernoulli beam theory)",
        "with bark + tremolo +",
        "amp tone."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Pads",
      "lines": [
        "Standard chromatic",
        "keyboard mapping.",
        "Notes 36-67 across",
        "the 32-pad grid.",
        "",
        "Pad pressure adds",
        "subtle bark, the",
        "harsh metallic attack",
        "the real 200A makes",
        "when played hard."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Knobs",
      "lines": [
        "K1 Volume",
        "K2 Tremolo",
        "    amplitude wobble",
        "    classic Wurli LFO",
        "K3 Attack",
        "    reed initial",
        "    motion time",
        "K4 Decay",
        "    reed damping",
        "K5 Brightness",
        "    treble lift",
        "K6 Darken",
        "    HF rolloff for",
        "    that midnight Wurli",
        "K7 Bark",
        "    velocity-driven",
        "    attack harshness",
        "K8 Reverb",
        "    spring-style tail"
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "About modal synthesis",
      "lines": [
        "The Wurli 200A's reed",
        "is a thin steel bar",
        "struck by a hammer.",
        "Its vibration is the",
        "sum of 7 vibrational",
        "modes at inharmonic",
        "frequency ratios.",
        "",
        "Modeled here via 7",
        "parallel resonators",
        "tuned to those modes.",
        "Each note retunes the",
        "whole bank, preserving",
        "the natural inhar-",
        "monicity that makes",
        "the Wurli sound like",
        "a Wurli."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Tips",
      "lines": [
        "Tremolo + Reverb is",
        " the classic Sun Ra",
        " / Ray Charles tone.",
        "",
        "Bark high + Brightness",
        " high + hard pads =",
        " Pink Floyd 'Money'",
        " grit.",
        "",
        "Darken pulls the high",
        " end down for a soft",
        " late-night ballad",
        " sound.",
        "",
        "Slow Attack adds bow-",
        " ed-string-style",
        " swell to each note."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
